1
00:00:20,186 --> 00:00:21,146
What?

2
00:00:23,106 --> 00:00:24,566
Ayana.

3
00:00:30,697 --> 00:00:31,573
Oh.

4
00:00:34,117 --> 00:00:36,953
Sorry. I'm leaving right now.

5
00:00:38,580 --> 00:00:41,291
No, I'm sorry too.

6
00:00:43,376 --> 00:00:46,546
I only came to check on her since I heard
that she's not feeling well.

7
00:00:47,422 --> 00:00:49,257
So, please don't leave for my sake.

8
00:00:49,340 --> 00:00:51,801
No, I'll be going now.

9
00:00:52,427 --> 00:00:53,303
Well,

10
00:00:53,928 --> 00:00:56,473
I don't think I should
stay here alone with her,

11
00:00:56,556 --> 00:00:57,599
so please stay.

12
00:00:59,309 --> 00:01:01,561
Are you serious?

13
00:01:02,562 --> 00:01:04,064
But you came to see her, right?

14
00:01:04,606 --> 00:01:05,565
Yeah,

15
00:01:06,816 --> 00:01:08,193
but really,

16
00:01:09,194 --> 00:01:10,403
please stay.

17
00:01:27,504 --> 00:01:29,088
Sorry for coming all of a sudden.

18
00:01:29,172 --> 00:01:30,089
Not at all.

19
00:01:32,759 --> 00:01:35,428
Nice to meet you. I'm Yamada.

20
00:01:36,304 --> 00:01:37,597
Nice to meet you.

21
00:01:38,223 --> 00:01:40,809
I'm Kotaro Hayase.

22
00:01:40,892 --> 00:01:41,935
Mr. Hayase.

23
00:01:42,018 --> 00:01:43,520
Yes, that's right.

24
00:01:48,775 --> 00:01:52,862
You're a hairstylist, right?

25
00:01:54,114 --> 00:01:55,698
Ah, yes.

26
00:01:56,407 --> 00:01:57,492
How do you know that?

27
00:01:58,326 --> 00:02:00,286
I heard about it from Ms. Tsuchida.

28
00:02:01,538 --> 00:02:02,455
Oh.

29
00:02:04,290 --> 00:02:05,291
Ayana told you?

30
00:02:06,501 --> 00:02:09,045
Ayana talked to you about me?

31
00:02:09,129 --> 00:02:10,130
Yeah.

32
00:02:12,549 --> 00:02:15,468
I see.

33
00:02:23,351 --> 00:02:25,812
Well, I've never really

34
00:02:25,895 --> 00:02:30,316
heard much about you.

35
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:32,110
Oh, sorry.

36
00:02:32,193 --> 00:02:34,571
That makes sense.

37
00:02:35,071 --> 00:02:40,201
I'm her colleague,

38
00:02:41,161 --> 00:02:43,163
and I'm also a writer.

39
00:02:43,246 --> 00:02:44,622
I write novels.

40
00:02:44,706 --> 00:02:46,791
Oh, I see.

41
00:02:47,876 --> 00:02:51,337
The thing is,
she doesn't tell me anything.

42
00:02:52,422 --> 00:02:54,632
I guess it's hard for her
to talk about it.

43
00:02:54,716 --> 00:02:57,385
She probably doesn't want me
to get jealous or anything.

44
00:02:57,468 --> 00:02:59,053
Jealous?

45
00:03:02,223 --> 00:03:05,560
Yeah. It would be no good
for me to get jealous.

46
00:03:07,103 --> 00:03:10,398
I mean, I'm in no position
to be getting jealous.

47
00:03:10,481 --> 00:03:11,774
But I get jealous easily.

48
00:03:27,832 --> 00:03:29,584
Can I ask you something a little weird?

49
00:03:30,084 --> 00:03:31,252
What is it?

50
00:03:32,337 --> 00:03:37,467
What do you like about Ms. Tsuchida?

51
00:03:38,343 --> 00:03:42,138
Or rather, what about her do you like?

52
00:03:44,766 --> 00:03:47,560
Huh? Why?

53
00:03:47,644 --> 00:03:48,895
Oh, sorry.

54
00:03:50,438 --> 00:03:52,899
I'm just simply curious.
There's no deep meaning to it.

55
00:03:54,567 --> 00:03:55,443
Huh?

56
00:03:56,945 --> 00:03:59,572
Um… excuse me.

57
00:04:00,823 --> 00:04:02,867
What has Ayana told you about me?

58
00:04:02,951 --> 00:04:04,285
I'm sorry for asking.

59
00:04:04,369 --> 00:04:06,412
You're probably thinking
I'm in no position to be asking.

60
00:04:06,496 --> 00:04:09,415
I don't care about that at all.

61
00:04:12,043 --> 00:04:13,878
Ms. Tsuchida told me that…

62
00:04:16,714 --> 00:04:17,715
How should I say this?

63
00:04:19,217 --> 00:04:20,843
She said

64
00:04:21,469 --> 00:04:25,348
that when she's with you,
time flows by peacefully.

65
00:04:26,599 --> 00:04:28,893
And that she feels at ease.

66
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:32,522
She said you're precious to her.

67
00:04:36,442 --> 00:04:37,443
What?

68
00:04:39,779 --> 00:04:43,366
Did Ayana really say that?

69
00:04:43,449 --> 00:04:45,410
Yeah, just now, in fact.

70
00:04:47,370 --> 00:04:48,413
Just now?

71
00:05:17,442 --> 00:05:18,484
What's wrong?

72
00:05:24,615 --> 00:05:26,409
Are you all right?

73
00:05:28,077 --> 00:05:29,120
Yeah.

74
00:05:29,787 --> 00:05:31,956
I'm sorry.

75
00:05:33,666 --> 00:05:35,418
She said that, huh?

76
00:05:38,629 --> 00:05:41,716
I really had no confidence in myself.

77
00:05:43,468 --> 00:05:46,804
I thought I was nothing
but a nuisance to Ayana.

78
00:05:47,472 --> 00:05:49,015
That's not true.

79
00:05:49,515 --> 00:05:51,684
But you know…

80
00:05:54,103 --> 00:05:56,814
hearing those words really saved me.

81
00:06:16,292 --> 00:06:17,960
- Um…
- Yes?

82
00:06:18,044 --> 00:06:20,713
I think I'll head out now.

83
00:06:20,797 --> 00:06:21,798
What?

84
00:06:21,881 --> 00:06:23,341
Please stay with her.

85
00:06:23,424 --> 00:06:27,595
I'm sure there are things
she wants to talk to you about.

86
00:06:28,096 --> 00:06:30,640
- What? But…
- No, I'm serious.

87
00:06:40,441 --> 00:06:41,609
Mr. Yamada.

88
00:06:43,402 --> 00:06:46,781
You must really trust Ayana.

89
00:06:47,698 --> 00:06:48,825
Trust?

90
00:06:50,910 --> 00:06:52,537
I don't really understand what you mean…

91
00:06:58,709 --> 00:07:00,211
Well, I'll be going.

92
00:08:31,177 --> 00:08:32,261
Ayana.

93
00:08:53,407 --> 00:08:54,450
You're finally awake.

94
00:08:59,580 --> 00:09:01,123
What's going on?

95
00:09:04,460 --> 00:09:06,295
Why are you here?

96
00:09:07,588 --> 00:09:09,924
Why are you inside my house?
You're scaring me.

97
00:09:10,967 --> 00:09:14,929
When I went to the shop,
En told me that you took a day off

98
00:09:15,596 --> 00:09:17,098
because you came down with a cold.

99
00:09:18,933 --> 00:09:20,518
Did you see anyone here?

100
00:09:20,601 --> 00:09:21,978
Was someone here when you came?

101
00:09:22,061 --> 00:09:25,273
Yeah, I think so.

102
00:09:26,399 --> 00:09:28,943
What? Did you talk to that person?

103
00:09:29,569 --> 00:09:30,778
Did you say anything?

104
00:09:30,861 --> 00:09:33,656
No, I didn't say anything. Nope.

105
00:09:34,448 --> 00:09:35,533
Are you serious?

106
00:09:35,616 --> 00:09:38,786
- This is the worst possible situation.
- Just calm down.

107
00:09:38,869 --> 00:09:42,123
Just be quiet
and listen to me for a second.

108
00:09:43,082 --> 00:09:44,041
What?

109
00:09:50,923 --> 00:09:55,761
I'm going to stop telling you

110
00:09:55,845 --> 00:09:58,347
how much I like you.

111
00:09:59,265 --> 00:10:00,891
I won't contact you anymore either.

112
00:10:00,975 --> 00:10:04,228
Although I won't reject you,
if you choose to contact me yourself.

113
00:10:05,354 --> 00:10:06,981
I like you

114
00:10:08,065 --> 00:10:10,151
but you're also very precious to me.

115
00:10:11,902 --> 00:10:13,779
And I've also realized

116
00:10:14,655 --> 00:10:17,742
that your boyfriend is a very nice person.

117
00:10:19,785 --> 00:10:22,663
It's not right for me to be jealous
of the happiness

118
00:10:24,874 --> 00:10:26,334
of someone I like.

119
00:10:34,675 --> 00:10:35,801
You're such a drag.

120
00:10:35,885 --> 00:10:39,096
So you two talked, didn't you?!

121
00:10:51,692 --> 00:10:55,112
Well, I'll be going now.

122
00:10:58,115 --> 00:11:00,242
- Hey, Kotaro.
- What is it?

123
00:11:01,786 --> 00:11:05,122
Well… Um…

124
00:11:06,916 --> 00:11:07,875
Well…

125
00:11:09,752 --> 00:11:12,630
As long as you know
that we can only be friends,

126
00:11:13,172 --> 00:11:15,341
you can feel free to contact me.

127
00:11:18,719 --> 00:11:20,179
Let's go out to eat or something.

128
00:11:22,264 --> 00:11:24,809
I don't think we should cut ties
or anything.

129
00:11:28,187 --> 00:11:29,939
When you're being a nuisance,

130
00:11:31,190 --> 00:11:35,653
or when I can't deal with you,
I might ignore you like I've always done.

131
00:11:41,117 --> 00:11:43,160
Okay, but I won't contact you myself.

132
00:11:44,078 --> 00:11:47,832
Because I still have feelings for you.

133
00:11:49,250 --> 00:11:51,001
That remains unchanged.

134
00:11:52,420 --> 00:11:55,172
I don't want to give your boyfriend
the wrong idea.

135
00:11:58,843 --> 00:12:01,220
How much did you hear from Mr. Yamada?

136
00:12:01,303 --> 00:12:03,264
Don't worry about anything.

137
00:12:03,347 --> 00:12:06,267
You know,

138
00:12:08,144 --> 00:12:09,687
I'm pretty happy right now.

139
00:12:11,564 --> 00:12:12,731
Bye.

140
00:13:19,882 --> 00:13:22,510
Just show it to me.

141
00:13:22,593 --> 00:13:23,677
You said you had a picture.

142
00:13:23,761 --> 00:13:25,804
Just show it to us. It's that simple.

143
00:13:28,807 --> 00:13:30,392
So dumb.

144
00:13:31,560 --> 00:13:34,355
It's not like I wanted to see it
that badly anyway.

145
00:13:34,438 --> 00:13:36,357
Who cares about your girlfriend anyway?

146
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:37,733
Seriously.

147
00:13:37,816 --> 00:13:42,655
We're just trying to have a conversation.
It's a form of communication.

148
00:13:43,322 --> 00:13:45,199
Stop putting up a wall. It's so dumb.

149
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:47,201
Then let's talk

150
00:13:48,577 --> 00:13:50,746
about something
other than my girlfriend's picture.

151
00:13:53,207 --> 00:13:54,124
Huh?

152
00:13:55,376 --> 00:13:56,585
What the hell?

153
00:14:00,548 --> 00:14:03,759
You think she's cute, right?
You should show her off.

154
00:14:06,262 --> 00:14:07,179
Hey.

155
00:14:08,013 --> 00:14:08,889
Hey!

156
00:14:09,682 --> 00:14:11,559
Don't you realize that you're being rude?

157
00:14:12,184 --> 00:14:15,729
Mr. Kawamura says he wants to see it,
so just show it to him.

158
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,815
You're no fun.

159
00:14:17,898 --> 00:14:20,317
Everything you do is always half-assed.

160
00:14:20,943 --> 00:14:23,737
And what was up with that document
you prepared yesterday?

161
00:14:23,821 --> 00:14:27,032
Are you making light
of our traditions and history?

162
00:14:27,116 --> 00:14:28,284
- Thank you.
- It's not something

163
00:14:28,367 --> 00:14:29,827
that can be changed so easily.

164
00:14:29,910 --> 00:14:32,037
You're just spouting your ideals.

165
00:14:32,121 --> 00:14:33,831
Yeah, what's your deal?

166
00:14:33,914 --> 00:14:36,083
- Thank you.
- Seriously.

167
00:14:36,792 --> 00:14:38,002
Seriously, what's wrong with you?

168
00:14:38,085 --> 00:14:39,253
Thank you.

169
00:14:40,462 --> 00:14:41,380
Hey.

170
00:14:42,923 --> 00:14:45,217
Hey.

171
00:14:45,301 --> 00:14:47,678
Excuse me.

172
00:14:47,761 --> 00:14:49,513
Yes? What is it?

173
00:14:49,597 --> 00:14:51,724
Well, um…

174
00:14:51,807 --> 00:14:53,475
I know this is none of my business,

175
00:14:53,559 --> 00:14:57,730
but I don't think you should hit people
over the head like that.

176
00:14:59,064 --> 00:14:59,940
Huh?

177
00:15:00,441 --> 00:15:03,110
I don't think it's right
to hit people like that.

178
00:15:05,154 --> 00:15:06,739
You guys were talking to him very rudely,

179
00:15:06,822 --> 00:15:10,034
and it just made me feel uncomfortable
listening to it.

180
00:15:10,117 --> 00:15:11,035
So, yeah…

181
00:15:12,745 --> 00:15:17,041
He was looking uncomfortable too,
so I thought I'd mention it.

182
00:15:17,124 --> 00:15:19,585
Oh wow, here's a Good Samaritan!

183
00:15:20,085 --> 00:15:23,005
Miss,
this is all part of training, got it?

184
00:15:23,088 --> 00:15:26,467
It's friendly banter.
We're good friends, okay?

185
00:15:26,967 --> 00:15:29,845
But yeah, Miss,
thank you for your concern.

186
00:15:32,181 --> 00:15:33,015
All right.

187
00:15:37,561 --> 00:15:40,230
TORA

188
00:15:54,745 --> 00:15:56,413
What? You said something?

189
00:15:57,498 --> 00:16:00,167
Yeah, although I was prepared
to make a quick escape.

190
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:03,212
Wow, you're so cool.

191
00:16:04,296 --> 00:16:06,256
But you shouldn't do that from now on.

192
00:16:06,340 --> 00:16:08,801
Your momentary sense of justice
can get you into trouble.

193
00:16:08,884 --> 00:16:10,803
I don't want you to get hurt.

194
00:16:11,387 --> 00:16:12,471
You're right.

195
00:16:13,514 --> 00:16:15,557
I was just getting over my cold,

196
00:16:15,641 --> 00:16:18,352
so I was a bit dazed,
which probably made me even more angry.

197
00:16:20,187 --> 00:16:23,315
But I think it's amazing.

198
00:16:23,899 --> 00:16:25,901
I'm sure that guy was happy too.

199
00:16:26,819 --> 00:16:27,861
Yeah.

200
00:16:41,333 --> 00:16:43,669
- Are you worried?
- What?

201
00:16:43,752 --> 00:16:45,337
You're worried, right?

202
00:16:45,421 --> 00:16:49,216
You're worried that he got
into more trouble after you left.

203
00:16:49,299 --> 00:16:52,386
After you left, they might've told him,
"You got us into trouble,"

204
00:16:52,469 --> 00:16:54,596
or "We were humiliated thanks to you."

205
00:16:55,097 --> 00:16:57,599
Yeah, that's what I'm worried about.

206
00:16:57,683 --> 00:16:58,851
That's a possibility.

207
00:17:00,144 --> 00:17:03,355
I see. I guess that's a possibility.

208
00:17:04,857 --> 00:17:06,233
That's too bad.

209
00:17:07,443 --> 00:17:09,653
Since all you did was try to help him.

210
00:17:14,366 --> 00:17:17,244
Showing the type of kindness that lasts,
is one thing.

211
00:17:17,745 --> 00:17:19,872
But it's difficult to show
the type of kindness

212
00:17:19,955 --> 00:17:21,290
that's momentary

213
00:17:21,373 --> 00:17:24,585
with no way of controlling its outcome.

214
00:17:26,754 --> 00:17:32,593
Then what should Ms. Ayana have done?

215
00:17:33,093 --> 00:17:33,969
What?

216
00:17:35,304 --> 00:17:38,265
There's someone in front of you
who's being treated badly,

217
00:17:38,348 --> 00:17:40,350
technically being bullied.

218
00:17:41,351 --> 00:17:43,520
Everyone there, including staff members,

219
00:17:43,604 --> 00:17:46,023
are turning a blind eye.

220
00:17:46,523 --> 00:17:50,444
Isn't it great that Ms. Ayana stood up
and took action in that situation?

221
00:17:52,237 --> 00:17:54,823
Are you saying that it was wrong
for her to show him kindness?

222
00:17:57,034 --> 00:18:00,079
Well, that's a possibility.

223
00:18:00,913 --> 00:18:02,664
There's no way! What?

224
00:18:02,748 --> 00:18:03,749
Wachi.

225
00:18:07,711 --> 00:18:10,881
I don't get it.

226
00:18:22,267 --> 00:18:25,229
It's not your fault, Ayana.

227
00:18:26,730 --> 00:18:30,526
You did the best you could at that moment.

228
00:18:34,947 --> 00:18:37,157
I wonder if it's really not my fault.

229
00:18:37,658 --> 00:18:39,243
Of course not.

230
00:18:49,044 --> 00:18:51,713
There are two types of kindness.

231
00:18:53,048 --> 00:18:55,259
Kindness that benefits this very moment,

232
00:18:55,884 --> 00:18:57,803
and kindness that benefits
in the long run.

233
00:18:59,096 --> 00:19:00,639
What En just said right now

234
00:19:00,722 --> 00:19:03,392
might be kindness that benefits
this very moment.

235
00:19:05,727 --> 00:19:08,939
You're right.

236
00:19:10,232 --> 00:19:13,735
But if we all start thinking like that,

237
00:19:15,070 --> 00:19:18,824
doesn't it make you hesitate
to act on behalf of others,

238
00:19:18,907 --> 00:19:21,076
or to approach others?

239
00:19:23,162 --> 00:19:25,831
Doesn't it make you hesitate
before giving up your seat on the train?

240
00:19:26,915 --> 00:19:28,834
No one can foresee the future.

241
00:19:31,503 --> 00:19:36,091
The kinder a person is, the more
they think about various possibilities,

242
00:19:36,175 --> 00:19:38,510
so I think it's hard for them to act.

243
00:19:39,428 --> 00:19:43,557
But I also think it's great
when people can act without worrying.

244
00:19:46,476 --> 00:19:50,522
There's no right answer. In fact,
there's more than one right answer.

245
00:20:19,843 --> 00:20:21,803
Kindness, huh.

246
00:20:40,697 --> 00:20:41,907
Hey.

247
00:20:42,532 --> 00:20:45,077
How many more balls of yarn should I buy?

248
00:20:46,203 --> 00:20:48,497
But I guess the longer the better, huh?

249
00:20:50,874 --> 00:20:52,417
- Hey.
- Yeah?

250
00:20:53,710 --> 00:20:57,589
The other day, I said that we shouldn't
see each other too often, didn't I?

251
00:20:58,382 --> 00:20:59,258
Is that right?

252
00:21:18,151 --> 00:21:19,695
It's still too short.

253
00:21:21,238 --> 00:21:22,906
I told you before

254
00:21:22,990 --> 00:21:25,867
that I can't stand things
that make my skin itch, didn't I?

255
00:21:25,951 --> 00:21:26,868
Is that right?

256
00:21:35,127 --> 00:21:36,253
Is that a gift?

257
00:21:36,336 --> 00:21:37,254
Yeah.

258
00:21:38,213 --> 00:21:39,381
For your boyfriend?

259
00:21:39,464 --> 00:21:41,008
Of course.

260
00:21:50,392 --> 00:21:51,518
Um…

261
00:21:52,602 --> 00:21:53,979
So…

262
00:21:54,688 --> 00:21:59,109
Mr. Yamada is a novelist like you, right?

263
00:21:59,901 --> 00:22:01,153
Mr. Yamada?

264
00:22:03,363 --> 00:22:04,489
Yeah, he is.

265
00:22:05,699 --> 00:22:08,493
I see. What kind of novels does he write?

266
00:22:09,619 --> 00:22:10,620
What kind?

267
00:22:10,704 --> 00:22:11,705
Yeah.

268
00:22:12,539 --> 00:22:13,999
What kind, huh…

269
00:22:14,666 --> 00:22:15,959
Yeah, what kind?

270
00:22:23,550 --> 00:22:25,385
His expressions are really subtle

271
00:22:26,636 --> 00:22:30,307
and often describe the feelings

272
00:22:30,390 --> 00:22:32,476
of people who overthink things.

273
00:22:33,477 --> 00:22:34,603
I see.

274
00:22:36,354 --> 00:22:37,814
It's mostly depressing.

275
00:22:38,774 --> 00:22:40,108
- Depressing?
- Yeah.

276
00:22:42,235 --> 00:22:44,613
Oh, and I think he makes an effort
to make things light.

277
00:22:45,697 --> 00:22:46,865
Light?

278
00:22:48,784 --> 00:22:50,035
You know,

279
00:22:50,118 --> 00:22:53,789
I think words have gravity.

280
00:22:54,706 --> 00:22:57,250
I've never
spoken to him about this directly,

281
00:22:58,543 --> 00:23:02,839
but I'm pretty sure he thinks
it's uncool to have words carry weight.

282
00:23:04,091 --> 00:23:05,217
I see.

283
00:23:07,260 --> 00:23:11,223
I don't get it at all.
It's depressing, but light?

284
00:23:12,599 --> 00:23:13,809
You'll get it if you read it.

285
00:23:26,404 --> 00:23:27,405
What's this for?

286
00:23:32,702 --> 00:23:33,620
Oh?

287
00:23:41,086 --> 00:23:44,089
PLEASE FEEL FREE TO USE THESE

288
00:23:46,258 --> 00:23:48,677
Oh wow! Look!

289
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:52,305
This is what that line is for.
Let's play this.

290
00:23:52,389 --> 00:23:54,808
No thanks. I suck at ping pong.

291
00:23:54,891 --> 00:23:57,018
Come on, let's just play one game.

292
00:23:57,102 --> 00:23:57,978
Fine.

293
00:24:00,063 --> 00:24:02,023
Here. Take this.

294
00:24:15,287 --> 00:24:16,788
It's so hard.

295
00:24:21,751 --> 00:24:23,920
- Oh, crap.
- Come on, play seriously.

296
00:24:24,004 --> 00:24:26,423
I am. I just suck at it.

297
00:24:26,506 --> 00:24:27,549
Are you serious?

298
00:24:29,009 --> 00:24:33,013
- I'm over it.
- Come on, stop sulking.

299
00:24:36,224 --> 00:24:37,392
Fine, I'll play by myself.

300
00:24:51,114 --> 00:24:53,200
Oh no!

301
00:24:53,283 --> 00:24:54,534
It rolled underneath.

302
00:25:03,585 --> 00:25:06,004
Can you get it?

303
00:25:13,011 --> 00:25:15,847
Back to the topic earlier about the novel…

304
00:25:15,931 --> 00:25:16,806
Yeah?

305
00:25:17,599 --> 00:25:20,644
Is that what you like about Mr. Yamada?

306
00:25:26,816 --> 00:25:28,151
I guess so.

307
00:25:30,987 --> 00:25:33,114
How long have you guys been going out?

308
00:25:33,198 --> 00:25:36,618
Huh? I'm not going out with him.

309
00:25:38,078 --> 00:25:40,956
Of course you are. Stop lying.

310
00:25:41,039 --> 00:25:43,583
I'm not lying.
Why'd you think that we're going out?

311
00:25:45,043 --> 00:25:47,587
What? Huh? What's going on?

312
00:25:48,964 --> 00:25:51,716
You're knitting that scarf
for Mr. Yamada, right?

313
00:25:52,300 --> 00:25:55,553
No, I already told you
I'm knitting it for my boyfriend.

314
00:25:55,637 --> 00:25:57,597
It's for your boyfriend, right?

315
00:25:57,681 --> 00:25:58,723
Yeah.

316
00:26:00,684 --> 00:26:01,559
Huh?

317
00:26:16,741 --> 00:26:20,036
Okay, let's stop for a second.
Let me figure this out.

318
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:23,415
So, let's see…

319
00:26:25,333 --> 00:26:27,210
On the day you had the fever,

320
00:26:27,294 --> 00:26:29,546
who was the man I met at your house?

321
00:26:30,588 --> 00:26:31,923
Mr. Yamada, right?

322
00:26:32,007 --> 00:26:34,926
That's Mr. Yamada, right?
And he's your boyfriend, right?

323
00:26:35,010 --> 00:26:37,762
I just told you that he's not.
Why do you think he is?

324
00:26:39,097 --> 00:26:41,599
Huh? Then…

325
00:26:42,642 --> 00:26:44,144
Who's your boyfriend?

326
00:26:44,853 --> 00:26:48,106
My boyfriend is someone else.
It's not Mr. Yamada.

327
00:26:53,403 --> 00:26:55,280
A new character suddenly appeared.

328
00:26:55,363 --> 00:26:56,197
Huh?

329
00:27:01,369 --> 00:27:04,247
Okay, sorry, I'm so confused.

330
00:27:04,331 --> 00:27:07,500
Can I ask you one more question?

331
00:27:07,584 --> 00:27:10,795
No, all of this is getting so annoying.

332
00:27:10,879 --> 00:27:16,134
Did you ever talk to Mr. Yamada about me?

333
00:27:16,634 --> 00:27:17,677
About you?

334
00:27:18,261 --> 00:27:19,471
Yeah.

335
00:27:19,554 --> 00:27:23,099
About how when we're together,

336
00:27:23,975 --> 00:27:26,478
the time just flows peacefully,

337
00:27:27,645 --> 00:27:29,647
and it makes you feel at ease.

338
00:27:32,984 --> 00:27:37,113
And how precious I am to you.
Did you say that to Mr. Yamada?

339
00:27:49,376 --> 00:27:51,002
Seriously?

340
00:28:00,095 --> 00:28:01,638
It's too funny.

341
00:28:04,599 --> 00:28:05,767
I'm doomed.

342
00:28:07,352 --> 00:28:09,479
- I'm doomed for sure.
- What the heck?

343
00:28:14,067 --> 00:28:16,319
Oh, it's snowing.

344
00:28:17,821 --> 00:28:20,156
- Yeah, you're right.
- Wow.

345
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:23,201
OGAWA LAUNDROMAT

346
00:28:23,284 --> 00:28:25,787
- Wow.
- Amazing.

347
00:28:26,871 --> 00:28:29,165
Wow, it's snowing a lot.

348
00:28:29,833 --> 00:28:30,834
Why?

349
00:28:33,169 --> 00:28:34,546
Do you think the snow will pile up?

350
00:28:34,629 --> 00:28:35,964
I doubt it.

351
00:28:36,047 --> 00:28:37,340
It probably will.

352
00:28:38,508 --> 00:28:39,342
It's freezing.

353
00:28:42,429 --> 00:28:45,098
Wow, it's probably going to snow a lot.

354
00:28:46,057 --> 00:28:48,810
It's amazing, huh?

355
00:28:51,229 --> 00:28:52,355
Hey.

356
00:28:59,237 --> 00:29:00,739
Stop eating it.

357
00:29:14,043 --> 00:29:15,211
Yes?

358
00:29:16,129 --> 00:29:19,007
I'm here to make a delivery.

359
00:29:19,090 --> 00:29:21,176
Please leave it at the door.

360
00:29:21,259 --> 00:29:22,844
Yes, will do.

361
00:29:22,927 --> 00:29:23,803
Thanks.

362
00:29:38,777 --> 00:29:40,153
- Hello?
<i>- I have a delivery.</i>

363
00:29:40,236 --> 00:29:41,154
Coming.

364
00:29:45,909 --> 00:29:48,578
Here's your package.

365
00:29:48,661 --> 00:29:50,830
- Please place it here.
- Okay.

366
00:29:52,165 --> 00:29:54,542
Please sign right here.

367
00:29:54,626 --> 00:29:55,710
Okay.

368
00:29:57,670 --> 00:29:58,546
Thank you.

369
00:29:58,630 --> 00:30:00,924
Thank you.

370
00:30:07,222 --> 00:30:08,681
You got a package?

371
00:30:08,765 --> 00:30:09,641
Yeah.

372
00:30:11,392 --> 00:30:12,519
Furniture.

373
00:30:12,602 --> 00:30:15,688
Furniture? You're not going to open it?

374
00:30:15,772 --> 00:30:18,316
I'll do it later.

375
00:30:19,192 --> 00:30:21,027
Let's eat first.

376
00:30:21,110 --> 00:30:22,904
Wow, that looks good.

377
00:30:22,987 --> 00:30:24,697
Yeah, because it's really good.

378
00:30:48,263 --> 00:30:50,682
- Thank you for the food.
- Let's eat.

379
00:31:08,741 --> 00:31:09,617
It's good.

380
00:31:27,051 --> 00:31:27,969
What is it?

381
00:31:32,849 --> 00:31:33,725
Sae?

382
00:31:39,939 --> 00:31:41,316
Can I open it?

383
00:31:41,399 --> 00:31:42,400
What?

384
00:31:42,483 --> 00:31:45,111
That box. Can I open it?

385
00:31:45,194 --> 00:31:46,029
What?

386
00:31:46,613 --> 00:31:49,032
You can, if you want.

387
00:31:50,575 --> 00:31:53,703
But let's eat first.
Or your food will get cold.

388
00:32:41,250 --> 00:32:42,293
<i>That chair…</i>

389
00:32:43,670 --> 00:32:44,837
<i>Yeah?</i>

390
00:32:44,921 --> 00:32:45,964
<i>I got that chair</i>

391
00:32:47,298 --> 00:32:49,717
last year on Christmas Eve.

392
00:32:50,510 --> 00:32:51,636
With Ayana.

393
00:32:53,262 --> 00:32:54,806
We bought two chairs.

394
00:32:55,348 --> 00:32:57,642
One for each of our houses.

395
00:32:59,519 --> 00:33:00,645
I see.

396
00:33:02,981 --> 00:33:06,150
So I think her chair
has been delivered to her house too.

397
00:33:07,694 --> 00:33:08,653
I see.

398
00:33:14,575 --> 00:33:16,285
Yeah,

399
00:33:17,954 --> 00:33:20,748
that's why I hesitated
to open it in front of you.

400
00:33:22,750 --> 00:33:24,043
That's all.

401
00:33:27,463 --> 00:33:28,631
I understand.

402
00:33:29,465 --> 00:33:31,676
Thank you for telling me.

403
00:33:48,985 --> 00:33:50,236
Mr. Yukio…

404
00:33:56,743 --> 00:33:58,870
You're really okay with it?

405
00:33:59,704 --> 00:34:00,705
Okay with what?

406
00:34:02,373 --> 00:34:05,668
Breaking up with Ms. Ayana.
You won't regret it?

407
00:34:06,502 --> 00:34:07,587
No, I won't.

408
00:34:09,547 --> 00:34:10,590
Really?

409
00:34:12,467 --> 00:34:14,719
Please don't lie to me.

410
00:34:16,512 --> 00:34:17,346
What?

411
00:34:19,682 --> 00:34:22,602
Please don't ever lie to me.

412
00:34:23,394 --> 00:34:26,022
Even if the truth will hurt me,

413
00:34:26,105 --> 00:34:27,732
I want you to be honest with me.

414
00:34:32,528 --> 00:34:33,446
Um…

415
00:34:35,281 --> 00:34:36,157
Um…

416
00:34:37,617 --> 00:34:38,910
But…

417
00:34:42,080 --> 00:34:43,039
Tell me the truth.

418
00:34:46,084 --> 00:34:47,710
Will you regret it or not?

419
00:34:53,674 --> 00:34:54,801
I don't know.

420
00:34:55,635 --> 00:34:57,345
Maybe I'll regret it.

421
00:35:00,389 --> 00:35:01,557
You still like her?

422
00:35:06,646 --> 00:35:07,855
Yeah.

423
00:35:09,190 --> 00:35:10,733
Maybe I still do.

424
00:35:14,737 --> 00:35:16,155
More than me?

425
00:35:25,414 --> 00:35:28,459
Of course. That's understandable.

426
00:35:33,422 --> 00:35:37,426
But now, I like you too.

427
00:35:43,891 --> 00:35:45,476
I'm really grateful to you.

428
00:35:48,813 --> 00:35:50,690
That's not a lie?

429
00:35:50,773 --> 00:35:52,191
It's the truth.

430
00:35:52,692 --> 00:35:55,194
I don't think I would've survived
without you, Sae.

431
00:35:57,822 --> 00:35:58,781
Yeah.

432
00:35:59,782 --> 00:36:01,284
You were struggling a lot.

433
00:36:02,368 --> 00:36:03,744
You lost weight too.

434
00:36:03,828 --> 00:36:04,912
Did I?

435
00:36:06,372 --> 00:36:07,582
Oh, really?

436
00:36:09,250 --> 00:36:11,961
I haven't weighed myself in a while.

437
00:36:30,855 --> 00:36:34,442
You must've really liked Ms. Ayana.

438
00:36:41,032 --> 00:36:45,661
But you like me too, right?

439
00:36:46,662 --> 00:36:50,166
You think you'll come
to like me too, right?

440
00:36:54,545 --> 00:36:58,216
I sound like a jerk for saying this,
but yeah, that's the truth.

441
00:37:02,220 --> 00:37:03,346
I'll believe in you.

442
00:37:12,730 --> 00:37:13,981
Sae.

443
00:37:14,065 --> 00:37:15,274
What is it?

444
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:18,694
When I break up with her…

445
00:37:18,778 --> 00:37:20,571
Once I'm able to break up with her,

446
00:37:22,490 --> 00:37:24,408
let's start dating.

447
00:37:26,077 --> 00:37:30,998
So can you wait a little longer?

448
00:37:37,880 --> 00:37:38,965
Of course.

449
00:37:55,398 --> 00:37:56,649
You're…

450
00:37:59,318 --> 00:38:01,237
You're so nice, Sae.

451
00:38:04,240 --> 00:38:06,158
No, I'm not.

452
00:38:08,160 --> 00:38:09,078
See?

453
00:38:11,539 --> 00:38:13,833
- I sat on this before you.
- Whoa.

454
00:38:13,916 --> 00:38:16,627
- I'm not a nice girl.
- You're the worst.

455
00:38:18,254 --> 00:38:20,548
- That's hilarious.
- Look.

456
00:38:22,300 --> 00:38:24,135
I'm totally sitting on it.

457
00:38:24,927 --> 00:38:29,307
What does that even mean?
It makes no sense.

458
00:38:37,815 --> 00:38:40,026
- Mr. Yukio.
- Yeah?

459
00:38:43,446 --> 00:38:44,989
I'll be totally okay.

460
00:38:46,866 --> 00:38:47,950
If you see her,

461
00:38:48,868 --> 00:38:50,661
and realize that you like her after all,

462
00:38:50,745 --> 00:38:52,663
and that you can't break up with her,

463
00:38:53,539 --> 00:38:58,169
then please continue going out with her.

464
00:39:01,839 --> 00:39:02,673
What?

465
00:39:06,260 --> 00:39:11,015
I want the person I like to be happy.

466
00:41:31,489 --> 00:41:35,576
WHAT SHOULD WE DO TOMORROW?

467
00:41:35,659 --> 00:41:36,994
WHERE AND WHAT TIME SHOULD WE MEET?

468
00:41:37,077 --> 00:41:40,956
READ

469
00:41:47,296 --> 00:41:53,469
HOW ABOUT THE LAUNDROMAT AT 2:00?

470
00:41:53,552 --> 00:42:00,309
THE LAUNDROMAT?

471
00:42:07,483 --> 00:42:12,905
YEAH, WHERE WE FIRST MET

472
00:42:12,988 --> 00:42:18,410
IS THAT OKAY?

473
00:42:18,494 --> 00:42:23,499
OKAY

474
00:42:24,500 --> 00:42:30,548
I'LL SEE YOU AT 2:00

475
00:42:40,140 --> 00:42:42,935
I WANT TO TALK TO YOU ABOUT SOMETHING

476
00:42:50,901 --> 00:42:57,866
OKAY, I DO TOO

477
00:44:37,758 --> 00:44:41,303
OGAWA LAUNDROMAT

478
00:47:34,309 --> 00:47:35,769
You fell asleep?

479
00:47:35,852 --> 00:47:37,229
Yeah, I fell asleep.

480
00:47:42,192 --> 00:47:43,527
I'm so sleepy.

481
00:47:45,821 --> 00:47:47,364
Then do you want to go home?

482
00:47:47,447 --> 00:47:48,907
Nope.

483
00:47:59,668 --> 00:48:01,044
It's sunny now.

484
00:48:03,672 --> 00:48:04,631
Yeah,

485
00:48:05,632 --> 00:48:06,800
it's sunny.

486
00:48:10,804 --> 00:48:13,390
I like sunny winter days the best.

487
00:48:14,516 --> 00:48:15,559
Winter?

488
00:48:17,102 --> 00:48:18,770
It's already March.

489
00:48:18,854 --> 00:48:20,397
So what if it's March?

490
00:48:21,273 --> 00:48:23,066
It's cold so it's still winter, damn it.

491
00:48:23,150 --> 00:48:24,401
You're so scary.

492
00:48:28,238 --> 00:48:29,698
- Let's go.
- Yeah.

493
00:48:36,288 --> 00:48:37,414
Oh.

494
00:48:41,001 --> 00:48:43,670
- Oh. That's…
- What is it?

495
00:48:44,671 --> 00:48:48,216
I lost that before. It's back again.

496
00:48:48,300 --> 00:48:49,843
Oh, really?

497
00:48:59,019 --> 00:49:01,104
Okay. Yukio.

498
00:49:04,358 --> 00:49:06,443
Happy Birthday.

499
00:49:06,526 --> 00:49:07,527
Thank you.

500
00:49:14,868 --> 00:49:16,036
Thank you.

501
00:49:35,097 --> 00:49:38,183
THIS DRAMA IS FICTIONAL

502
00:49:38,266 --> 00:49:39,142
Subtitle translation by: Lili Morita
